verses.text_plain: Then Jacob went on his journey, and came into the land of the people of the east.
verses.verse_html:
1Then Jacob went on his journey, and came into the land of the people of the east. ▼
▼ went…: Heb. lift up his feet
 , ▼
▼ people: Heb. children

footnotes.body_text: ▼ went…: Heb. lift up his feet
footnotes.body_html: ▼ went…: Heb. lift up his feet

verses.text_plain: And he looked, and behold a well in the field, and, lo, there were three flocks of sheep lying by it; for out of that well they watered the flocks: and a great stone was upon the well’s mouth.
verses.verse_html: 2And he looked, and behold a well in the field, and, lo, there were three flocks of sheep lying by it; for out of that well they watered the flocks: and a great stone was upon the well’s mouth.

tokens.text: by it; for out of that well

verses.text_plain: And thither were all the flocks gathered: and they rolled the stone from the well’s mouth, and watered the sheep, and put the stone again upon the well’s mouth in his place.
verses.verse_html: 3And thither were all the flocks gathered: and they rolled the stone from the well’s mouth, and watered the sheep, and put the stone again upon the well’s mouth in his place.

tokens.text: And thither were all the flocks

verses.text_plain: And Jacob said unto them, My brethren, whence be ye? And they said, Of Haran are we.
verses.verse_html: 4And Jacob said unto them, My brethren, whence be ye? And they said, Of Haran are we.

verses.text_plain: And he said unto them, Know ye Laban the son of Nahor? And they said, We know him.
verses.verse_html: 5And he said unto them, Know ye Laban the son of Nahor? And they said, We know him.

verses.text_plain: And he said unto them, Is he well? And they said, He is well: and, behold, Rachel his daughter cometh with the sheep.
verses.verse_html:
6And he said unto them, Is he well? And they said, He is well: and, behold, Rachel his daughter cometh with the sheep. ▼
▼ Is he…: Heb. Is there peace to him?

footnotes.body_text: ▼ Is he…: Heb. Is there peace to him?
footnotes.body_html: ▼ Is he…: Heb. Is there peace to him?

verses.text_plain: And he said, Lo, it is yet high day, neither is it time that the cattle should be gathered together: water ye the sheep, and go and feed them.
verses.verse_html:
7And he said, Lo, it is yet high day, neither is it time that the cattle should be gathered together: water ye the sheep, and go and feed them. ▼
▼ it is…: Heb. yet the day is great

footnotes.body_text: ▼ it is…: Heb. yet the day is great
footnotes.body_html: ▼ it is…: Heb. yet the day is great

verses.text_plain: And they said, We cannot, until all the flocks be gathered together, and till they roll the stone from the well’s mouth; then we water the sheep.
verses.verse_html: 8And they said, We cannot, until all the flocks be gathered together, and till they roll the stone from the well’s mouth; then we water the sheep.

verses.text_plain: And while he yet spake with them, Rachel came with her father’s sheep: for she kept them.
verses.verse_html: 9And while he yet spake with them, Rachel came with her father’s sheep: for she kept them.

verses.text_plain: And it came to pass, when Jacob saw Rachel the daughter of Laban his mother’s brother, and the sheep of Laban his mother’s brother, that Jacob went near, and rolled the stone from the well’s mouth, and watered the flock of Laban his mother’s brother.
verses.verse_html: 10And it came to pass, when Jacob saw Rachel the daughter of Laban his mother’s brother, and the sheep of Laban his mother’s brother, that Jacob went near, and rolled the stone from the well’s mouth, and watered the flock of Laban his mother’s brother.

tokens.text: And it came to pass, when Jacob

verses.text_plain: And Jacob kissed Rachel, and lifted up his voice, and wept.
verses.verse_html: 11And Jacob kissed Rachel, and lifted up his voice, and wept.

verses.text_plain: And Jacob told Rachel that he was her father’s brother, and that he was Rebekah’s son: and she ran and told her father.
verses.verse_html: 12And Jacob told Rachel that he was her father’s brother, and that he was Rebekah’s son: and she ran and told her father.

verses.text_plain: And it came to pass, when Laban heard the tidings of Jacob his sister’s son, that he ran to meet him, and embraced him, and kissed him, and brought him to his house. And he told Laban all these things.
verses.verse_html:
13And it came to pass, when Laban heard the tidings of Jacob his sister’s son, that he ran to meet him, and embraced him, and kissed him, and brought him to his house. And he told Laban all these things. ▼
▼ tidings: Heb. hearing

tokens.text: And it came to pass, when Laban

verses.text_plain: And Laban said to him, Surely thou art my bone and my flesh. And he abode with him the space of a month.
verses.verse_html:
14And Laban said to him, Surely thou art my bone and my flesh. And he abode with him the space of a month. ▼
▼ the space…: Heb. a month of days

footnotes.body_text: ▼ the space…: Heb. a month of days
footnotes.body_html: ▼ the space…: Heb. a month of days

verses.text_plain: And Laban said unto Jacob, Because thou art my brother, shouldest thou therefore serve me for nought? tell me, what shall thy wages be?
verses.verse_html: 15And Laban said unto Jacob, Because thou art my brother, shouldest thou therefore serve me for nought? tell me, what shall thy wages be?

verses.text_plain: And Laban had two daughters: the name of the elder was Leah, and the name of the younger was Rachel.
verses.verse_html: 16And Laban had two daughters: the name of the elder was Leah, and the name of the younger was Rachel.

verses.text_plain: Leah was tender eyed; but Rachel was beautiful and well favoured.
verses.verse_html: 17Leah was tender eyed; but Rachel was beautiful and well favoured.

verses.text_plain: And Jacob loved Rachel; and said, I will serve thee seven years for Rachel thy younger daughter.
verses.verse_html: 18And Jacob loved Rachel; and said, I will serve thee seven years for Rachel thy younger daughter.

verses.text_plain: And Laban said, It is better that I give her to thee, than that I should give her to another man: abide with me.
verses.verse_html: 19And Laban said, It is better that I give her to thee, than that I should give her to another man: abide with me.

tokens.text: her to thee, than that I should give

verses.text_plain: And Jacob served seven years for Rachel; and they seemed unto him but a few days, for the love he had to her.
verses.verse_html: 20And Jacob served seven years for Rachel; and they seemed unto him but a few days, for the love he had to her.

verses.text_plain: And Jacob said unto Laban, Give me my wife, for my days are fulfilled, that I may go in unto her.
verses.verse_html: 21And Jacob said unto Laban, Give me my wife, for my days are fulfilled, that I may go in unto her.

verses.text_plain: And Laban gathered together all the men of the place, and made a feast.
verses.verse_html: 22And Laban gathered together all the men of the place, and made a feast.

verses.text_plain: And it came to pass in the evening, that he took Leah his daughter, and brought her to him; and he went in unto her.
verses.verse_html: 23And it came to pass in the evening, that he took Leah his daughter, and brought her to him; and he went in unto her.

tokens.text: And it came to pass in the evening
her to him; and he went in

verses.text_plain: And Laban gave unto his daughter Leah Zilpah his maid for an handmaid.
verses.verse_html: 24And Laban gave unto his daughter Leah Zilpah his maid for an handmaid.

verses.text_plain: And it came to pass, that in the morning, behold, it was Leah: and he said to Laban, What is this thou hast done unto me? did not I serve with thee for Rachel? wherefore then hast thou beguiled me?
verses.verse_html: 25And it came to pass, that in the morning, behold, it was Leah: and he said to Laban, What is this thou hast done unto me? did not I serve with thee for Rachel? wherefore then hast thou beguiled me?

tokens.text: And it came to pass, that in the morning
unto me? did not I serve

verses.text_plain: And Laban said, It must not be so done in our country, to give the younger before the firstborn.
verses.verse_html:
26And Laban said, It must not be so done in our country, to give the younger before the firstborn. ▼
▼ country: Heb. place

tokens.text: It must not be so done

verses.text_plain: Fulfil her week, and we will give thee this also for the service which thou shalt serve with me yet seven other years.
verses.verse_html: 27Fulfil her week, and we will give thee this also for the service which thou shalt serve with me yet seven other years.

tokens.text: thee this also for the service

verses.text_plain: And Jacob did so, and fulfilled her week: and he gave him Rachel his daughter to wife also.
verses.verse_html: 28And Jacob did so, and fulfilled her week: and he gave him Rachel his daughter to wife also.

verses.text_plain: And Laban gave to Rachel his daughter Bilhah his handmaid to be her maid.
verses.verse_html: 29And Laban gave to Rachel his daughter Bilhah his handmaid to be her maid.

verses.text_plain: And he went in also unto Rachel, and he loved also Rachel more than Leah, and served with him yet seven other years.
verses.verse_html: 30And he went in also unto Rachel, and he loved also Rachel more than Leah, and served with him yet seven other years.

verses.text_plain: And when the Lord saw that Leah was hated, he opened her womb: but Rachel was barren.
verses.verse_html: 31And when the Lord saw that Leah was hated, he opened her womb: but Rachel was barren.

verses.text_plain: And Leah conceived, and bare a son, and she called his name Reuben: for she said, Surely the Lord hath looked upon my affliction; now therefore my husband will love me.
verses.verse_html:
32And Leah conceived, and bare a son, and she called his name Reuben: for she said, Surely the Lord hath looked upon my affliction; now therefore my husband will love me. ▼
▼ Reuben: that is, See a son

footnotes.body_text: ▼ Reuben: that is, See a son
footnotes.body_html: ▼ Reuben: that is, See a son

verses.text_plain: And she conceived again, and bare a son; and said, Because the Lord hath heard that I was hated, he hath therefore given me this son also: and she called his name Simeon.
verses.verse_html:
33And she conceived again, and bare a son; and said, Because the Lord hath heard that I was hated, he hath therefore given me this son also: and she called his name Simeon. ▼
▼ Simeon: that is, Hearing

footnotes.body_html: ▼ Simeon: that is, Hearing

verses.text_plain: And she conceived again, and bare a son; and said, Now this time will my husband be joined unto me, because I have born him three sons: therefore was his name called Levi.
verses.verse_html:
34And she conceived again, and bare a son; and said, Now this time will my husband be joined unto me, because I have born him three sons: therefore was his name called Levi. ▼
▼ Levi: that is, Joined

tokens.text: unto me, because I have born

footnotes.body_html: ▼ Levi: that is, Joined

verses.text_plain: And she conceived again, and bare a son: and she said, Now will I praise the Lord: therefore she called his name Judah; and left bearing.
verses.verse_html:
35And she conceived again, and bare a son: and she said, Now will I praise the Lord: therefore she called his name Judah; and left bearing. ▼
